HMDA Case Study Series: Interactive Visualizations

Let’s look at some interactive plots from a sample taken from our HMDA case study series for Vermont loans in 2012 using rCharts.

This is a fun interactive scatter plot of the relationship between loan amount and income with the icons representing the loan purpose. The bubble icon represents home purchase while the blue line represents home improvement while the green dots represent refinancing. If you click on the icons at the botttom of the plot, various displays of the data are shown using the D3 library under the hood.

This interactive scatterplot is representing the relationship between loan amount and income grouped by which agency originated the loan. Clicking on the agency name at the bottom of the chart shows different displays of the data based on agency name.

This multi-Bar Horizontal chart shows the number of loan originations of each agency in our sample by the purpose of the loan. Different representations of the data can be viewed by clicking on the loan purpose name in the top right corner and other information can be viewed by hovering over the bars.

This is a faceted bar plot of loan amount by loan purpose name faceted by agency name. Hovering over the bars display more information about the plot.
